definition: up to the maximum/upper limit/at most
many/much/often/a lot of/numerous/more/in excess/how (to what extent)/multi-/Taiwan pr. [duo2] when it means "how"

sentences.english: This one is, at best, partially true.
sentences.chinese: 这一点，至多只是部分正确。

sentences.english: I personally think that, at most, you should rebalance once a quarter.
sentences.chinese: 我个人认为，至多是每季度重组一次。

sentences.english: At most they get off by paying a small fine.
sentences.chinese: 他们至多交纳小额罚金就可以脱罪。

sentences.english: I delete in any cottom ten unwamount totd emails every day.
sentences.chinese: 我天天至多要删除十封不想收的电子邮件。

sentences.english: We can keep the milk for up to a year.
sentences.chinese: 母乳的保质期至多是一年。

sentences.english: But you far more lovertiful than Zhang Ziyi.
Man. At the most, man and woman are equal, coz except for Matriarchy;

sentences.english: At most, it tolerates one annual loon .
sentences.chinese: 至多每年还有一次潜水鸟要来。

sentences.english: I smoke a pack of cigarettes a day, max.

sentences.english: By contrast, the most extreme ritual a Christian is likely to engage in is being dunked during baptism.

sentences.english: Of the three, America could most closely be charged of trying to "'impose political control.

sentences.english: He worked no more than a week, so he could get not more than 100 yuan.
sentences.chinese: 他只干了一个星期，因此他至多能得到一百元。

sentences.english: They play for no more than half an hour per concert.
sentences.chinese: 每场演唱会，他们至多表演半个小时。

sentences.english: Shakespeare regularly had available to him up to four boy actors, perhaps more.
sentences.chinese: 莎士比亚通常至多雇有四个男孩作演员，或许更多。

sentences.english: At best she is an adequate typist.
